00:00:28,370 --> 00:00:30,080
stockholders.

12
00:00:30,080 --> 00:00:34,530
So cash is going to go up by $24,000.

13
00:00:34,530 --> 00:00:36,080
So when you're doing these things,

14
00:00:36,080 --> 00:00:38,270
always keep track of cash first.

15
00:00:38,270 --> 00:00:41,860
So it's always easy to see what happened to cash.

16
00:00:41,860 --> 00:00:44,450
Now we got to do something to balance the balance sheet

17
00:00:44,450 --> 00:00:45,890
equation.

18
00:00:45,890 --> 00:00:48,520
What would that something be?

19
00:00:48,520 --> 00:00:50,870
Well, we sold some stock.

20
00:00:50,870 --> 00:00:53,710
So then we know that that stock sale is going

21
00:00:53,710 --> 00:00:56,050
to go into contributed capital.

22
00:00:56,050 --> 00:00:58,440
And to make the balance sheet equation balance,

23
00:00:58,440 --> 00:01:01,920
